The paper discusses methods for diversifying latent variable models, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes Bayesian approaches for achieving diversity in these models, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses regularization and overfitting, which are common topics in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses variational inference and MCMC sampling, which are common methods in the field of Statistics (cs.ST). The paper also discusses mutual angular prior, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses Bayesian nonparametric models, which may fall under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
